        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 4:33PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 433 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northwest of Burnsville, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ramseytown.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
